"not even think about\" escaping blame by claiming the tapes were edited.</p><p>Turkey's main opposition party, the Republican People's party, held an emergency meeting late on Monday and called on Erdogan to resign, saying the government had lost its legitimacy.</p><p>\"Turkey cannot carry on with this blemish and this burden,\" senior party official Haluk Koc said.</p><p>The  audio recordings reportedly took place on 17 December,  following the arrests of three cabinet ministers' sons in a police corruption and bribery probe.</p><p>Erdogan insists the corruption investigation targeting people close to him is a conspiracy against his government ahead of local elections in March and an August presidential election .</p><p>The government says the investigations were orchestrated by followers of a moderate Islamic movement, led by US-based cleric Fethullah Gulen,  which has allegedly infiltrated Turkey's police and judiciary.</p>","headline":"Turkish opposition calls for Erdogan to be investigated for corruption","trailText":"Embattled prime minister claims voice recordings of him ordering his son to dispose of large sums of cash are fabricated","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/2/25/1393330732817/Recep-Tayyip-Erdogan-002.jpg","wordcount":"239","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-02-28T12:29:01Z"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/feb/25/recep-tayyip-erdogan-investigated-corruption-turkey","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/world/2014/feb/25/recep-tayyip-erdogan-investigated-corruption-turkey","tags":[{"id":"world/recep-tayyip-erdogan","webTitle":"Recep Tayyip Erdogan","type":"keyword","sectionId":"world","sectionName":"World news","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/world/recep-tayyip-erdogan","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/world/recep-tayyip-erdogan","references":[]},{"id":"world/turkey","webTitle":"Turkey","type":"keyword","sectionId":"world","sectionName":"World new